comment.author: 43685624@N06
comment._content:
Nancy Bird was born in Kew NSW 16/10/1915. Her "A" Private Licence was No:1150 issued 29/9/1933 (at age 17), her "B" Commercial Licence was No:494 issued 21/3/1935 (age age 19) making Nancy the youngest Australian woman pilot in the British Commonwealth. She was the first Australian woman to "use" her commercial pilot's licence when she went barnstorming in her Gipsy Moth VH-UTN. She upgraded to a Leopard Moth VH-UGG when contracted to pioneer the air ambulance service for the Far West Children's Health Scheme, based in Bourke NSW, at age 20. 

The youngest Australian woman pilot is reported to have been in SA on 5/4/1932 No:920, a Miss J Scott-Kemball.

Any Australian woman pilot history questions, feel free to ask me.

comment.author: 43685624@N06
comment._content:
P.S: Jean Burns is reported to be the youngest Australian woman pilot when she obtained her Licence No:2128 on 18/3/1937 in Victoria. Jean was born in November 1919. There is a street named after her at Essendon Airport.

"Youngest" seems to be taken as at the date attained? Anyone's guess!

However, Jean was the first Australian woman to parachute from a plane.
